userStories.notes:
Two-part change.

Part 1: In platform/mcp-server/src/logger.ts, add a private helper to format args:

const formatArgs = (args: unknown[], includeStack: boolean): unknown[] => {
  const last = args[args.length - 1];
  if (last instanceof Error) {
    const rest = args.slice(0, -1);
    if (includeStack && last.stack) {
      return [...rest, last.message + '\n  ' + last.stack];
    }
    return [...rest, last.message];
  }
  return args;
};

Then in each method, use formatArgs:
- debug: console.debug(TAG, ts, ...formatArgs(args, true))  — include stack
- info:  console.log(TAG, ts, ...formatArgs(args, false))    — no stack
- warn:  console.warn(TAG, ts, ...formatArgs(args, false))   — no stack
- error: console.error(TAG, ts, ...formatArgs(args, false))  — no stack (stack visible at debug level)

Part 2: Update all callsites across the MCP server. Search for the pattern:
  err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)
and replace with just `err`. Files to check:
- platform/mcp-server/src/reload.ts (~5 places)
- platform/mcp-server/src/extension-protocol.ts (~5 places)
- platform/mcp-server/src/discovery.ts (~3 places)
- platform/mcp-server/src/mcp-setup.ts (~3 places)
- platform/mcp-server/src/file-watcher.ts (~2 places)
- platform/mcp-server/src/http-routes.ts (~2 places)
- platform/mcp-server/src/config.ts (~1 place)
- platform/mcp-server/src/extension-install.ts (~2 places)
- platform/mcp-server/src/index.ts (~1 place)

The pattern is always the same: change
  log.error('Failed to X:', err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err))
to:
  log.error('Failed to X:', err)

Also check for bare err.message usage (without the instanceof guard).
